USiQ6FimeDr-I2HLpY8M8IfGAa9SQsR45o9OEFurYwjZndVF5-JOnRgEw1l8Y4K28cYoMz4aeFxFs8Q_l0UP_-rc0OppQb-B3NYZ34OiiT09VxcrAUeaWcLQPMUMucfdOecZJDa3IfDz5alItYpTS2y-4Xvs\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing native image dependencies**\\n\\nI'm considering the dependency on javassist and its reference to the jdk.jdi module for native image analysis with HotSwapper. I wonder if native-image includes modules that are present in classpath references. It seems like it encounters a NoClassDef issue. I think that if a class isn't found during the image build, it might be okay as long as it's not loaded until runtime. This seems worth further exploration to clarify how it all interacts!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating JDI Types**\\n\\nI'm considering whether I require JDI types. It seems like it might need the VirtualMachine field, especially since native-image analysis has to load the bytecode and associated types. I wonder if the jdk.jdi module is included in the default root modules; it might not be. Maybe I should add `testRuntimeOnly`? Hmm, I should also check to see if there are similar tests for the jdk modules that I could reference.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_IvJaHqjCNfRhRBOsD9LX6zuC|fc_0197830a069ce5a00169f51632cc8c819c88981e573a6b7962", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg -n \"HotSwapper|com.sun.jdi|IllegalConnectorArgumentsException|jdk.jdi|--add-modules\" tests/src metadata -S", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1240, "output": 1148, "cacheRead": 15872, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 18260, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777669663288, "responseId": "resp_0197830a069ce5a00169f5161fa420819c98b5898bbd0a94a5"}}
